The paper discusses a method for calculating myopic value of information in influence diagrams, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI). The use of junction trees and table expansion also suggests a connection to probabilistic graphical models and inference algorithms (cs.LG). The paper also involves decision making and optimization (cs.DM), as well as information theory (cs.IT) in the calculation of expected utility. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to social influence and network analysis (cs.SI) due to the use of influence diagrams.
